cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with pose tracking using keypoint information. It may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as pose tracking is an important problem in robotics. The use of a Transformer-based network for binary classification suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper's focus on real-time tracking may suggest it belongs to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the use of benchmarks and evaluation metrics suggests it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
